  <title translate="true">Decimal-Symbol</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><table styleclass="MotionPupup" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Decimal symbol</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> - the symbol that separates the number digits that are greater or equal to 0 from the number digits that are less than 0.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">UK, the default </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Decimal Symbol</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is a &apos;.&apos; (Stop, or Period(USA))</text></para>
          <para styleclass="" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Europe: the default </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Decimal Symbol</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is a &apos;,&apos; (comma)</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName-small"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">In Excel</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">&#32;</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">By default, Microsoft Excel uses the system separators that are defined in the regional settings in Control Panel. If you sometimes need to display numbers with different separators for thousands or decimals, you can temporarily replace the system separators with custom separators. In Excel:</text></para>
          <list id="58" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Click </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">File &gt; Options</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">On the </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Advanced</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> tab, under </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Editing options</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">, clear the </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Use system separators</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> check box.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Type new separators in the </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Decimal separator</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Thousands separator</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> boxes.</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Tip</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">:</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> When you want to use the system separators again, select the </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Use system separators </text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">check box.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Note</text><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true">:</text><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">For a permanent solution, you must change the </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">regional settings</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> in Windows </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Control Panel.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"></para>
        </td>
